46
00:04:39,510 --> 00:04:42,350
I forgot to ask for his number.

47
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,870
S-Senior?

48
00:05:01,870 --> 00:05:03,830
Are you trash?

49
00:05:03,830 --> 00:05:06,050
Pardon me?

50
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:09,400
Why are you charging towards the dumpster?

51
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:15,070
Oh. H-How is it that you're here?

52
00:05:15,710 --> 00:05:19,920
I have no idea who put a dumpster in the middle of the road.

53
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:23,850
It'll be bad if anyone crashes into it.

54
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:31,350
I don't have his number. Ask for it yourself.

55
00:05:31,350 --> 00:05:33,480
Hanging up.

56
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:43,550
Senior.

57
00:05:43,550 --> 00:05:49,420
Your phone...

58
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:51,110
What?

59
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:59,480
Y-Y-Your... Does your home phone work?

60
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:01,930
I have a relative that sells telephones.

61
00:06:01,930 --> 00:06:03,350
What?

62
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:07,140
How did you know that our house phone recently broke?

63
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:11,520
But I've already fixed it.

64
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:13,150
Oh, I see.

65
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:16,930
I'm off.

66
00:06:16,930 --> 00:06:20,350
Bye, Senior.

67
00:07:04,790 --> 00:07:07,510
It's so late. What were you up to?

68
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:11,110
A student was tutoring me.

69
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:14,560
Tutoring?

70
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:17,910
Then how did your clothes end up like this?

71
00:07:17,910 --> 00:07:22,080
Can't you just kindly appreciate the results of my hard work?

72
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:25,710
If you really are going for tutoring like this every day...

73
00:07:25,710 --> 00:07:28,700
In the entire grade, only two people failed the exam

74
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:31,580
and you're one of them!

75
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:36,670
Explain yourself. Come, tell me.

76
00:07:41,350 --> 00:07:43,500
I...

77
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:47,470
You what?

78
00:07:47,470 --> 00:07:51,080
Aren't you usually pretty good with words?

79
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:55,730
When the teacher called me, at first, I felt quite understanding and forgiving.

80
00:07:55,730 --> 00:08:00,710
After all, we have just moved here and you just transferred. Your poor exam results were forgivable.

81
00:08:00,710 --> 00:08:03,830
But Xia Miaomiao, you can't lie to me!

82
00:08:03,830 --> 00:08:07,340
You can't go out and play and tell me that you were studying.

83
00:08:07,340 --> 00:08:10,260
I really was studying.

84
00:08:12,820 --> 00:08:17,060
You're really insisting that you were studying? Fine, give me that person's number.

85
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:19,450
Give it to me. I'll call him myself.

86
00:08:19,450 --> 00:08:23,150
I am going to ask him just what exactly he's tutoring you in!

87
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:30,120
What? Don't you have it?

88
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:35,320
You... and that Xia Santu.

89
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:38,790
Can't you two make me not worry so much?

90
00:08:38,790 --> 00:08:40,970
It's so late, and you're going out to play!

91
00:08:40,970 --> 00:08:43,270
You don't even know to call home if you're late!

92
00:08:43,270 --> 00:08:45,210
Not calling you is to give you a surprise.

93
00:08:45,260 --> 00:08:47,500
Not calling you is to give you a surprise.

94
00:08:47,540 --> 00:08:49,300
Dad!

95
00:08:53,260 --> 00:08:54,030
- Dad.
- Yes?

96
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:56,970
How come you suddenly came back?

97
00:08:56,970 --> 00:09:00,430
There was a tropical cyclone, so we turned the boat back.

98
00:09:00,450 --> 00:09:02,140
Thank you, cyclone.

99
00:09:02,140 --> 00:09:05,020
Why didn't you call if you were coming back?

100
00:09:05,020 --> 00:09:06,580
Where is Yaoyao?

101
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:09,710
Isn't she the same as you, both of you don't like to stay home.

102
00:09:09,710 --> 00:09:12,230
What great genes.

103
00:09:12,940 --> 00:09:14,230
- Miaomiao.
- Yes?

104
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:18,500
- How are your scores after transferring schools?
- Don't bring this up.

105
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:22,800
She failed math on her finals. A re-test?

106
00:09:22,820 --> 00:09:27,460
I mean, what's the point of even applying to a university? After she graduates high school, she can just work for me in this store.

107
00:09:27,460 --> 00:09:31,170
- Wouldn't it be great if you became a waitress with me?
- Okay, enough.

108
00:09:31,170 --> 00:09:37,080
Oh, right. I haven't eaten yet tonight. Why don't you make me two dishes?

109
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:40,300
All of you only know how to open your mouths and eat.

110
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:44,160
If you don't want me to talk, just say it directly.

111
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:46,730
Stop with the "Oh, I haven't eaten yet."

112
00:09:46,730 --> 00:09:48,220
Would we even be able to carry on with our lives this way?

113
00:09:48,220 --> 00:09:50,110
Yes, you can.

114
00:09:50,110 --> 00:09:54,140
I saw on the internet that a lot of customers gave you a high rating.

115
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:56,910
Isn't that all because of you?

116
00:09:56,910 --> 00:10:00,060
Stop trying to flatter me.

117
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,820
Wait.

118
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:12,440
Hey!

119
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:15,550
Hurry and hide it, hide it.

120
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:20,390
You can't let your mom see or else she'll come after me.

121
00:10:20,390 --> 00:10:22,800
Your teeth aren't great, yet I still bring you chocolate.

122
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:26,100
Mom wants me to wear braces.

123
00:10:29,390 --> 00:10:31,820
Your mom is doing it for your good.

124
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:33,740
Don't you know your mother well?

125
00:10:33,740 --> 00:10:36,240
She sounds harsh but she has a good heart.

126
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:40,210
Every day, she saves up and spends frugally,

127
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:43,500
just so she can save money to get you braces.

128
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:46,830
Just then, your mother talked about you not getting into a university,

129
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:50,670
but actually, her heart is always worried about you.

130
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:56,070
Actually, I know all of these.

131
00:10:56,100 --> 00:11:01,250
Miaomiao, don't give yourself that much pressure.

132
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:07,150
First, think about what you really want to do and then work hard.

133
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,440
Hey?

134
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:17,310
Dad!

135
00:11:19,210 --> 00:11:21,790
How come you came home?

136
00:11:21,790 --> 00:11:24,560
Where did you go so late? Huh?

137
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:32,420
Look at you, those who don't know what's going on might think that I abused you.

138
00:11:32,420 --> 00:11:35,140
You treat me like a stepmother every day.

139
00:11:35,140 --> 00:11:37,470
Have you eaten?

140
00:11:38,230 --> 00:11:40,660
Let's eat together. Come, come.

141
00:11:40,660 --> 00:11:42,410
- I want to eat, too.
- Okay.

142
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:46,740
- Stop adding yourself to the trouble.
- Who's going to have the first bite?

143
00:11:46,740 --> 00:11:48,610
Me!

144
00:11:48,610 --> 00:11:51,170
- You can't eat it. You can't eat it.
- I'm going to eat it!
- No!

145
00:11:51,170 --> 00:11:53,470
Then I'll eat it!

146
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:09,350
Red.

147
00:12:48,090 --> 00:12:52,990
The next time I see Senior, I will definitely get his number.

148
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:11,330
Miaomiao, don't put too much pressure on yourself.

149
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:17,900
Think about what you want to do and then work hard.

150
00:13:20,870 --> 00:13:24,190
Senior is such a brilliant person,

151
00:13:24,190 --> 00:13:27,550
he definitely knows what he wants to do with his life.

